#CHIP RF5C164
#CLOCK 7670453

; RF5C164 (Sega CD PCM) Basic Test
;
; The RF5C164 is a Ricoh chip used in the Sega CD (Mega CD) for PCM audio.
; It has 8 channels of 8-bit PCM playback with a sample rate of 32kHz.
;
; Tests:
; - All 8 channels with basic sample playback
; - Volume control
; - Pan positioning

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; Channel 1: Sample playback
c4 .

; Channel 2: Different sample
c4 .

; Channel 3: Another sample
d4 .

; Channel 4: Yet another sample
e4 .

r4

; All 8 channels together
c4 & c4 & d4 & e4 & f4 & g4 & a4 & b4 .

r4

; Volume sweep test
; Play same sample at different volumes
c4 . c4 . c4 . c4 .

r2

#END
